from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import math
import pandas as pd
from scipy.optimize import curve_fit
from mpmath import *
import cmath
i=complex(0,1)
name='Loaded Cable 1k-200M.csv'
df=pd.read_csv(name,sep=',')
df

f=np.array(df['Frequency (Hz)'])
Rs=df['Rs (Ohm)']
Zs=df['Xs (Ohm)']

fig, ax=plt.subplots()

ax.plot(f,Rs, color='b', label='Real Part')
ax2=ax.twinx()
ax2.plot(f,Zs,color='r',label='Imaginary Part')

plt.title('Impedance vs. Frequency for Loaded Cable')
ax.set_xlabel('Frequency (Hz)')
ax.set_ylabel('Re(Impedance) (ohms)')
ax2.set_ylabel('Im(Impedance) (ohms)')

ax2.legend(loc='upper left')
ax.legend(loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(1.4, 0.8), shadow=True, ncol=1)
ax2.legend(loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(1.4, .7), shadow=True, ncol=1)

fig, ax=plt.subplots()

y=loaded_cable(f,5.52831225e-10,5.50757577e-08)
plt.plot(f,y.real,color='maroon',label='Resistance "Fit"')
plt.plot(f,y.imag,color='blue',label='Reactance "Fit"')
plt.scatter(f,Rs,s=1,color='red', label='Resistance Measurements')
plt.scatter(f,Zs,s=1,color='navy',label='Reactance Measurements')

plt.title('Impedance vs. Frequency for Loaded Cable')
ax.set_xlabel('Frequency (Hz)')
ax.set_ylabel('Re(Impedance) (ohms)')
ax.legend(loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(1.5, 0.8), shadow=True, ncol=1)

paramR, param_covR = curve_fit(Reloaded_cable,f,Rs,p0=(5.52831225e-10,5.50757577e-08), maxfev=100000*len(f))
paramI, param_covI = curve_fit(Imloaded_cable,f,Zs,p0=(5.52831225e-10,5.50757577e-08), maxfev=100000*len(f))

fig, ax=plt.subplots()

yR=Reloaded_cable(f,paramR[0],paramR[1])
yI=Imloaded_cable(f,paramI[0],paramI[1])

plt.plot(f,yR,color='orange',label='Resistance Fit')
plt.plot(f,yI,color='yellow',label='Reactance Fit')
plt.scatter(f,Rs,s=1,color='red', label='Resistance Measurements')
plt.scatter(f,Zs,s=1,color='blue',label='Reactance Measurements')

plt.title('Low Loss Best Fit of Impedance for Loaded Cable')
ax.set_xlabel('Frequency (Hz)')
ax.set_ylabel('Re(Impedance) (ohms)')
ax.legend(loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(1.5, 0.8), shadow=True, ncol=1)

# residuals
fig, ax=plt.subplots()
resRE=Rs-yR
resIm=Zs-yI
plt.scatter(f,resRE,s=1,color='purple',label='For Resistance')
plt.scatter(f,resIm,s=1,color='pink',label='For Reactance')

plt.title('Residuals for Low-Loss Model of Impedance of Loaded Cable')
ax.set_xlabel('Frequency (Hz)')
ax.set_ylabel('Residual (ohms)')
ax.legend(loc='upper right')
